Have you heard about Black Nurses Week™ and the Black Nurses Week Conference?

Black Nurses Week was created by Black nursing professionals with the goal of designating a specific week out of the year to celebrate and shine the light on Black nursing excellence. Black Nurses Week will be celebrated each year from July 26 - August 1. 

And, if you’re looking to build your community and knowledge base, the second annual Black Nurses Week Conference will be held in Washington, DC from July 27-31, 2023. This year’s theme is ‘Opportunities Beyond the Bedside 2.0’ and we’ll honor Black nursing professionals in every field and specialty.  We’ll learn the tips and strategies you need to explore what your nursing experience can do for you away from a clinical setting. 

I’m so excited to be a part of this event and would love for you to join me. To learn more and to register, visit www.blacknursesweek.com.
.
.

Will nurses be replaced by AI??

Artificial Intelligence has the power and potential to greatly impact the nursing profession. Will robots 🤖 or computers 💻 replace nurses as caregivers at the bedside? Doubtful.

What nurses CAN do is to leverage #AI to help intervene for patients earlier and improve patient outcomes. AI can also streamline appropriate staffing and optimize scheduling, as well as personalize education and feedback for nurses in real-time.

Tell us your thoughts on AI and how you see it impacting the future of nursing ⬇️ ⬇️

So many people are getting into entrepreneurship for a lifestyle, not understanding that entrepreneurship looks different for everyone. 

Some people work 24/7 while others work 4 hour days. Some people travel for work while others are holed up in a small office chugging away. Some people get success early while many others have to toil away for years. 

Being an entrepreneur means that you can do things your way & build it how you want to. Don’t buy into the hype. Invest in the process & not just the people who are doing what you want to do. 

Do you know people who keep paying for success but still aren’t successful?

📸 @esterelphoto
